headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis had 30 points and 13 rebounds and the Washington Wizards routed the short-handed Orlando Magic 119-100 on Friday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis, Wizards beat Magic 119-100 for 4th straight win

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — LeBron James started this journey 20 years ago, and there are times when he still feels like a kid on the basketball court.
headlines.shortLinkText: James has season-high 47 on 38th birthday, Lakers beat Hawks

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. matched his season high with 35 points, Pascal Siakam had 26 and the Toronto Raptors snapped a five-game home losing streak with a 113-104 victory over the short-handed and sloppy Phoenix Suns on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent scores 35 points, Raptors beat short-handed Suns

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored a season-high 43 points, and the Chicago Bulls pulled away in the closing minutes to beat the Detroit Pistons 132-118 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores season-high 43 as Bulls beat Pistons 132-118

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 43 points and 20 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks snapped a four-game losing streak with a 123-114 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has 43 and 20, Bucks snap 4-game skid

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 42 points, making a franchise-record and career-high 11 3-pointers, and Zion Williamson added 36 to power the New Orleans Pelicans to a 127-116 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Friday night.
— Jamal Murray struggled to find his range or rhythm for most of the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Jokic help Nuggets rally for 124-119 win over Heat

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — The Golden State Warriors have been working to find their defensive groove, and Draymond Green leads the charge. On Friday night, Green and his supporting cast got it done in crunch time.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole scores 41, Thompson 31, Warriors beat Blazers 118-112

headlines.description: — Kevin Huerter hit a 3-pointer with 9.2 seconds left and the Sacramento Kings held off Utah 126-125 on Friday night when Jazz forward Lauri Markkanen missed a jumper in the final seconds.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Huerter hits late 3-pointer, Kings beat Jazz 126-125
